                        "type": "1",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "<p>The nurse is planning to instruct a mental health client and his or her family about the importance of medication compliance. The nurse should plan for which interventions that are associated with increased compliance? Select all that apply.</p>",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "<p>Rationale:</p><p>Including the family in the medication planning process; providing clients with the injectable, long-acting form of the medication; and finding the right medication at the right dose that provides the fewest side effects for the client are measures that will promote compliance. Not all medications can be given on a once-per-day dosing regimen because of their short half-life.</p><p><br></p><p>Client Needs: Safe and Effective Care Environment</p><p>Clinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Generate Solutions</p><p>Cognitive Ability: Analyzing</p><p>Content Area: Mental Health</p><p>Integrated Process: Nursing Process/Planning</p><p>Priority Concepts: Adherence, Safety</p><p>Strategies: Subject</p><p><br></p><p>Test-Taking Strategy:</p><p>Focus on the subject, medication compliance, and read each option carefully. Thinking about the variations in the half-life of medications will assist in answering correctly.</p><p> </p>",
